Weekend Observance
•
If a holiday falls on a Saturday, it will be observed on the preceding Friday.
•
If a holiday falls on a Sunday, it will be observed on the following Monday.
Floating Holidays
•
Each employee receives 2 floating holidays per calendar year in addition to the standard public holidays.
•
Floating holidays can be used on any day the employee chooses, subject to manager approval.
•
Floating holidays must be used within the calendar year and do not carry over.
•
Floating holidays are available from January 1 of each year.
Additional Company Holidays
In addition to federal holidays, Acme Corp observes the following company-wide days off:
•
Day after Thanksgiving (Friday following Thanksgiving Thursday)
•
Christmas Eve (December 24)
•
End-of-Year Break: December 26 through December 31 (employees do not need to use PTO for these days)
This gives employees a full week off at the end of December each year.
Holiday Pay
•
Full-time employees receive their regular daily rate of pay for each observed holiday.
•
Employees who are required to work on a public holiday will receive 1.5× their regular hourly rate for hours worked on that day, plus the holiday may be rescheduled at a later date with manager approval.
Part-Time Employees
•
Part-time employees who are regularly scheduled to work on the day a holiday falls will receive holiday pay for their normally scheduled hours.
•
Part-time employees not scheduled to work on a holiday do not receive holiday pay for that day.
New Employees
•
New employees are eligible for holiday pay from their first day of employment.
•
There is no waiting period for holiday entitlement.
International Employees
•
Employees based outside the United States follow the public holiday calendar for their country of employment.
•
International employees should refer to their local addendum or contact HR for their specific holiday schedule.
